=\"font-size:20px;\"><a href=\"#section-three\"><b>3. Process Phase</b></a></span>\n    * <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"#subsection-three-one\">1.1 Main tools of processing</a></span>\n    * <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"#subsection-three-two\">1.2 Assissing data stage</a></span>\n        * <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"#subsection-three-two-one\">1.2.1 Importing and inspecting the dataset</a></span>\n        * <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"#subsection-three-two-two\">1.2.2 The data types require cleaning</a></span>\n        * <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"#subsection-three-two-three\">1.2.3 Missing values</a></span>\n        * <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"#subsection-three-two-four\">1.2.4 Unique values</a></span>\n        * <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"#subsection-three-two-five\">1.2.5 Duplicate values</a></span>\n        * <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"#subsection-three-two-six\">1.2.6 Check a sample of the dataset</a></span>\n        * <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"#subsection-three-two-seven\">1.2.7 Check the number of inactive usage days</a></span>     \n    * <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"#subsection-three-three\">1.3 Cleaning data stage</a></span>\n        * <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"#subsection-three-three-one\">1.3.1 Correcting the data types</a></span>\n        * <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"#subsection-three-three-two\">1.3.2 Cleaning column names</a></span>\n        * <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"#subsection-three-three-three\">1.3.3 Dropping duplicate values</a></span>\n        * <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"#subsection-three-three-four\">1.3.4 Removing inaccurate records</a></span>\n        * <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><a href=\"#subsection-three-three-five\">1.3.5 Merging tables</a></span>\n* <span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><a href=\"#section-four\"><b>4. Analyze Phase</b></a></span>\n* <span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><a href=\"#section-five\"><b>5. Share Phase</b></a></span>\n* <span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><a href=\"#section-six\"><b>6. Final Insights and recommendations</b></a></span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"093264c7-8e34-4066-aeee-dd5aadcfec21","_cell_guid":"d0ee5e14-8392-45a5-b385-579a37514b8f","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<hr>","metadata":{"_uuid":"bc05d202-a36a-4fc6-a97e-311d79813394","_cell_guid":"5ace2a9e-7a45-4160-9a82-ba3b0519c459","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# <span style=\"color:#FFBF00; font-size:27px; font-family:sans-serif;\"><a id=\"introduction\"> </a> Overview </span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"fac42b7b-f29a-4529-805c-0fc4ae9816dc","_cell_guid":"35a38335-1f37-4d9b-b07e-955f67d1ba11","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Bellabeat** is high-tech company that manufactures health-focused smart products. Collecting data on activity, sleep, stress, and reproductive health has allowed Bellabeat to empower women with knowledge about their own health and habits. The company develops wearables and accompanying products that monitor biometric and lifestyle data to help women better understand how their bodies work and make healthier choices.","metadata":{"_uuid":"dcbac08f-c50a-48bc-bef2-8975a729a283","_cell_guid":"193f893c-3098-4673-bb36-0537f08cfac3","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<hr>","metadata":{"_uuid":"13dcc780-76c8-49d1-8675-57449d3b9c54","_cell_guid":"9efdf7c1-40fb-437e-a09c-8f14fe5f84d2","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"![Ask](https://img.freepik.com/free-vector/hand-drawn-people-asking-questions-illustration_23-2148906555.jpg?t=st=1651920604~exp=1651921204~hmac=72886d5f9f8e6425757923e83210a73bfe4dea8792a41047728a3e71d8bd8701&w=996)\n*Source:* <a href=\"https://www.freepik.com/vectors/human-illustration\">Human illustration vector created by freepik - www.freepik.com</a>","metadata":{"_uuid":"ebdd2a55-a684-45f0-822a-1b47ba447af3","_cell_guid":"eb2e0ad8-bafb-449d-87e5-6addddbc4574","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# <span style=\"color:#FFBF00; font-size:27px; font-family:sans-serif;\"><a id=\"introduction\"> </a> Ask Phase </span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"4851aa5e-87fd-4927-9aab-d781dab27ac6","_cell_guid":"e8c9862d-0066-4f33-895a-ab2dbac6b958","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"subsection-one-one\"></a>\n###  **What is the goal of this project *(Business Task)?***","metadata":{"_uuid":"5d47d6b6-7954-464c-93ed-06c5fad15ebc","_cell_guid":"c58f9503-7384-4a2e-84a5-e199bf9d6573","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"The goal of this project is to study the trends and patterns of smart wearable devices usage to figure out the most used features. These trends will then be applied to **Bellabeat** consumers to devise marketing strategy that can comply with the wishes and aspirations of Bellabeat current or projected consumers. The study will be applied on 30 of **FitBit** users. By figuring out the pattern of usage of these users, this study can propose effective solutions to **Bellabeat** stakeholders to promote the marketing strategy.","metadata":{"_uuid":"1480d993-18de-409a-a4f4-43494cd2e1fc","_cell_guid":"fd0e3d29-c4f5-4dce-b102-149fda2bd573","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"subsection-one-two\"></a>\n###  **What are the main business questions?**","metadata":{"_uuid":"ddbae879-30f0-4356-af75-682b2021d7f8","_cell_guid":"55eda161-8c04-4c50-a637-d4b37205db15","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"1. What are some trends in smart device usage?\n2. How could these trends apply to Bellabeat customers?\n3. How could these trends help influence Bellabeat marketing strategy?","metadata":{"_uuid":"e4b314d7-9c2a-4d0e-90f1-39df0b3b6340","_cell_guid":"c20ce5cb-309b-4603-a9ff-50d3bd9bee04","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"subsection-one-three\"></a>\n###  **Who are the key stakeholders?**","metadata":{"_uuid":"c238be3a-0fca-4693-b538-e9d1a61bcfd8","_cell_guid":"7883f028-bb7b-4915-b5d4-edd3a114baa7","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"-\t**Urška Sršen:** Bellabeat’s cofounder and Chief Creative Officer\n-\t**Sando Mur:** Bellabeat’s cofounder; key member of the Bellabeat executive team.\n-\t**Bellabeat marketing analytics team**","metadata":{"_uuid":"73b759af-867a-4880-986e-3edbac3e5db3","_cell_guid":"bccc7af0-69a0-4ad5-96ab-24f55ef77ed5","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<hr>","metadata":{"_uuid":"d0549b2b-376c-4b40-b3a5-f3834affded8","_cell_guid":"c8bf291f-cb21-4001-bab9-80d827ceb9b7","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"![Prepare](https://img.freepik.com/free-vector/business-performance-analysis-with-graphs_53876-66263.jpg?t=st=1651921141~exp=1651921741~hmac=080466aa78eb1898797e9a66cdd0a0f3318f72e4efc72a54744652673fcf1ed6&w=996)\n*Source:* <a href=\"https://www.freepik.com/vectors/data-report\">Data report vector created by rawpixel.com - www.freepik.com</a>","metadata":{"_uuid":"7fec53ff-3e94-44bf-bfe8-e7a6e870142e","_cell_guid":"4e05bbec-11b0-40e2-81c3-5dbbbdfa2280","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# <span style=\"color:#FFBF00; font-size:27px; font-family:sans-serif;\"><a id=\"introduction\"> </a> Prepare Phase </span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"b3833033-b9ca-4260-a798-dfabde0678fb","_cell_guid":"39f9481b-8fe8-4535-aebe-a461c34ec34f","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"subsection-two-one\"></a>\n###  **About the dataset**","metadata":{"_uuid":"1f505829-142f-4d24-b2a3-8b29ecf8f543","_cell_guid":"bc724bb3-c47c-415f-bca7-513fa0ed96fc","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"This project utilizes the [FitBit Fitness Tracker Data](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/arashnic/fitbit) provided by [Möbius](https://www.kaggle.com/arashnic), a data scientist at *Healthcare in Melbourne, Australia*. The data is generated by respondents to a distributed survey via *Amazon Mechanical Turk*. The data used in this project is based on both daily and hourly scale and it is demonstrated in the below tables. According to the dataset publisher, **Thirty eligible Fitbit users consented to the submission of personal tracker data, including minute-level output for physical activity, heart rate, and sleep monitoring**.\n\nThe dataset used in this project is described at the demonstrated table below.","metadata":{"_uuid":"d6acabdc-0559-4823-8f02-adb2f1240703","_cell_guid":"408713c9-ec85-41a9-b36c-60dd5edc9364","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"| Table Name             | File Type  | Description  |\n|:----------------------:|:-----------:|:-------------:|\n|dailyActivity_merged    |CSV file     |Contains daily totals for steps, intensity, distance, and calories. The data is recorderd for 31 days from 12th of April to 12th of May for 33 users|\n|sleepDay_merged         |CSV file     |Contains the sleep records for 8 unique users|\n|weightLogInfo_merged    |CSV file     |Contains the following data: the *weight* is recorded for both Kilogram and Pounds, the *body fat* percentage, *BMI* (Body Mass Index), *IsManualReport* is the logical value for the recorded report if it is recorded manually or by Fitbit, and the *LogId* is unique log id in Fitbit system|\n|hourlyIntensities_merged |CSV file     |Contains the following data: *ActivityHour* records Date and hour value in mm/dd/yyyy hh:mm format,*TotalIntensity* is the value calculated by adding all the minute-level intensity values that occurred within the hour,*AverageIntensity* is the average intensity state exhibited during that hour (*TotalIntensity* for that *ActivityHour* divided by 60)|\n|hourlySteps_merged  |CSV file   |Contains the total number of steps taken for the given hour|\n|hourlyCalories_merged  |CSV file    |Contains the total amount of calories burnt for the given hour|\n\nSource: https://www.fitabase.com/media/1930/fitabasedatadictionary102320.pdf By [Laimis Andrijauskas](https://www.kaggle.com/laimisandrijauskas)","metadata":{"_uuid":"a6febe64-b2c3-4e2a-b178-a18b1eaf9ac9","_cell_guid":"b207308f-269e-4848-addf-e7f050631cd9","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"subsection-two-two\"></a>\n### **Data privacy and storage**","metadata":{"_uuid":"f73bcad8-40fb-47ba-8c2e-05095b8a347a","_cell_guid":"52fb0ebd-bf4c-4414-a1db-fee0fbdc59e6","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"The data is stored in *OneDrive* account to ensure the multi-layer safety of the data.\nThis data is collected and published under the consent of the users. In addition, the personal data of these users *(e.g. names, addresses, …)* are not provided in this dataset.","metadata":{"_uuid":"1fca78b6-55d1-4d3b-91a0-dfe028211f13","_cell_guid":"b210061f-747b-49f2-bd0d-f630b1d0dde7","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"subsection-two-three\"></a>\n### **Data verification and organization**","metadata":{"_uuid":"fb867991-9f0e-425c-a5b3-f8568e8c6a2f","_cell_guid":"139cf980-2868-49ea-9c0a-439b81ef4245","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Data is visually and programmatically assessed by *Microsoft Excel* and *Microsoft SQL* to check for the quality and tidiness of the data. The data used in this project is structured and in a long format.\n\nAs for the data source, there are some criteria that should be present in any data source to be called *“good”* data source. These criteria are called *“ROCCC”* and by applying this term on our data source to explain it below:\n\n**Reliable:** This data source suffers from the problem of biasedness as the data collected are from men only and there are some tables that have missing values. Therefore, this dataset is not lacks demographic information that can make it reliable enough for Bellabeat Company.\n\n**Original:** This data can be called original as it is validated with the original source.\n\n**Comprehensive:** The sample size of this data is very little to make accurate generalizations. However, the sample size of 33 can be near the minimum acceptable sample size according to the **Central Limit Theorem (CLT)**, which is 30 observations. \n\n**Current:** The data is collected about 6 years ago. Therefore, It does not comply with this criterion as well.\n\n**Cited:** our dataset is cited from the publisher and is given the consent of the users to be published. So, our data passes this criterion successfully.\nDespite these limitations, this project will continue to provide the stakeholders with the insights that we can gain from this dataset.","metadata":{"_uuid":"b3ed103b-20b7-466b-aa50-892ae59eaf89","_cell_guid":"cb1baf4c-7d38-4a66-b518-2211c52bb638","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<hr>","metadata":{"_uuid":"8099807c-9605-476b-a53a-168b6d78327f","_cell_guid":"d99f3fec-f553-4f29-b667-919633f9e3cf","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"![Process](https://img.freepik.com/free-vector/business-team-working-as-mechanism_1262-19220.jpg?t=st=1651922084~exp=1651922684~hmac=7334a8046fd596bee9d96f612811c8df78896ac2ec7d5892886f5fdc865e488a&w=996)\n*Source:* <a href=\"https://www.freepik.com/vectors/work-process\">Work process vector created by katemangostar - www.freepik.com</a>","metadata":{"_uuid":"c4ee321a-40a9-4548-9b24-26ac7d4b9699","_cell_guid":"0e045f65-825d-4aa4-b934-61e3aa61480e","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# <span style=\"color:#FFBF00; font-size:27px; font-family:sans-serif;\"><a id=\"introduction\"> </a> Process Phase </span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"5cec8cae-db43-4d63-aa93-bbef2146d4a7","_cell_guid":"baffdc26-47f6-4ee3-b00b-d8a131ab52af","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"subsection-three-one\"></a>\n### **Main tools of processing**","metadata":{"_uuid":"b273edb5-c672-47bc-b5df-ed52864cd38c","_cell_guid":"32b435cb-a3e2-4176-9de0-16cbc3214440","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Microsoft Excel:** to visually assess the dataset and figure out the structure and shape of the data.\n\n**Microsoft SQL:** to double check the data and figure out possible relationships among variables from different tables.\n\n**R prgramming language:** which will be used through the rest of the project to double assess, clean, and build visualization of our data.","metadata":{"_uuid":"17a99b17-e283-401c-a451-32f10d735db2","_cell_guid":"87e455fb-d3c4-47d3-9616-4bdd87994e8d","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"subsection-three-two\"></a>\n### **Assessing data stage**","metadata":{"_uuid":"07babf54-79d2-4ec7-bdb2-9aaacfea5cb8","_cell_guid":"539f8311-5ef9-4a5d-bb87-1b516664a46a","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<span style=\"font-size:17px;\"><a id = \"subsection-three-two-one\"></a><u><b>Importing and inspecting the dataset</b></u></span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"63c51a77-e4d4-44a1-9b37-d4063a7450be","_cell_guid":"a8dd9a65-9f48-4872-84d3-f00f27359389","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"devtools::install_github(\"kassambara/ggpubr\")","metadata":{"_uuid":"334fc5fc-3750-4652-bc35-ec36b60cea3d","_cell_guid":"9c255eb0-f45f-4504-be94-e56826b315e8","collapsed":false,"_kg_hide-output":true,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:54:32.3716Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:54:32.373569Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:22.368643Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Importing the libraries used for processing\nlibrary(tidyverse)\nlibrary(dplyr)\nlibrary(skimr)\nlibrary(readr)\nlibrary(janitor)\nlibrary(lubridate)\nlibrary(magrittr)\nlibrary(ggrepel)\nlibrary(ggpubr)","metadata":{"_uuid":"e48a0fc1-2186-47a8-887e-d01b47149f1e","_cell_guid":"f7c6274d-fafa-4ffe-a58b-0d791d8839c4","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:22.374042Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:22.377075Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:23.617069Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Import the dataset\ndaily_activity <- read_csv('../input/fitbit/Fitabase Data 4.12.16-5.12.16/dailyActivity_merged.csv')\ndaily_sleep <- read_csv('../input/fitbit/Fitabase Data 4.12.16-5.12.16/sleepDay_merged.csv')\nweight_log <- read_csv('../input/fitbit/Fitabase Data 4.12.16-5.12.16/weightLogInfo_merged.csv')\nhourly_steps <- read_csv('../input/fitbit/Fitabase Data 4.12.16-5.12.16/hourlySteps_merged.csv')\nhourly_calories <- read_csv('../input/fitbit/Fitabase Data 4.12.16-5.12.16/hourlyCalories_merged.csv')\nhourly_intensities <- read_csv('../input/fitbit/Fitabase Data 4.12.16-5.12.16/hourlyIntensities_merged.csv')","metadata":{"_uuid":"cd7002c0-764e-426d-8227-8589832a3ca0","_cell_guid":"4e4107a0-4d68-4ece-85d4-b5b7ebc9f342","collapsed":false,"_kg_hide-output":true,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:23.619711Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:23.621574Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:24.489111Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"The dataset that we will work on is as follows:\n\n* 3 tables that record the activities of users on **daily basis.**\n\n* 3 tables that record the activities of users on **hourly basis.**","metadata":{"_uuid":"98bdc1cc-9fd1-410b-9605-c7e509d589ab","_cell_guid":"f546c13b-5ecc-4a57-9952-c39d4884d3a4","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<span style=\"font-size:17px;\"><a id = \"subsection-three-two-two\"></a><u><b>The datatypes require cleaning</b></u></span>\n* `ActivityDate` column in `daily_activity` table is *chr* instead of *datetime*.\n* `SleepDay` column in `daily_sleep` table is *chr* instead of *datetime*.\n* `Date` column in `weight_log` table is *chr* instead of *datetime*.\n* `Activityhour` column in `hourly_steps` table is *chr* instead of *datetime*.\n* `ActivityHour` column in `hourly_calories` table is *chr* instead of *datetime*.\n* `ActivityHour` column in `hourly_intensities` table is *chr* instead of *datetime*.","metadata":{"_uuid":"0492d952-30c3-4488-bccd-0f13519f0f8e","_cell_guid":"8503c6f2-6652-46cf-b169-cdfcd098b3f9","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Checking for the datatypes\nglimpse(daily_activity) # ActivityDate is chr instead of datetime\nglimpse(daily_sleep) # SleepDay is chr instead of datetime\nglimpse(weight_log) # Date is chr instead of datetime\nglimpse(hourly_steps) # ActivityHour is chr instead of datetime\nglimpse(hourly_calories) # ActivityHour is chr instead of datetime\nglimpse(hourly_intensities) # ActivityHour is chr instead of datetime","metadata":{"_uuid":"1048d240-e7bf-4db1-be6f-57a2dcf773a0","_cell_guid":"b2f37d7f-66ad-41e1-8fe5-4ce159e6e50e","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:24.493997Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:24.497681Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:24.573639Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<span style=\"font-size:17px;\"><a id = \"subsection-three-two-three\"></a><u><b>Missing values</b></u></span>\n\n* `weight_log` table is te only table that contains missing values in `Fat` column with 65 missing values, which is big number compared to the total observation, which are 67.\n* Dealing with missing values is by interpolating, taking an average of the rest of observations, or by removing them.","metadata":{"_uuid":"e1ca5457-c2ad-4a1a-8651-d3380b730328","_cell_guid":"1d65f696-da44-4b67-bbca-3a2912b18590","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Checking for missing values\nsum(is.na(daily_activity))\nsum(is.na(daily_sleep))\nsum(is.na(weight_log)) # 65 missing values\nsum(is.na(hourly_steps))\nsum(is.na(hourly_calories))\nsum(is.na(hourly_intensities))","metadata":{"_uuid":"e6ae5952-7339-4e95-8b85-487b0b320360","_cell_guid":"ae738f30-d4dc-4658-b564-d42a55938706","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:24.576212Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:24.577727Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:24.641182Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Figure out the column with missing values in weight_log\nnames(which(colSums(is.na(weight_log))>0))","metadata":{"_uuid":"a13d5b65-6e45-4926-9008-2362e07426e0","_cell_guid":"bdc9dd4d-ee86-4278-9e59-d957032ac7ef","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:24.643588Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:24.645012Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:24.660795Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<span style=\"font-size:17px;\"><a id = \"subsection-three-two-four\"></a><u><b>Unique values</b></u></span>\n\n* Now we need to check the number of unique users that their activities are recorded and included in the dataset.\n\n* All tables have *33 unique users* that their activities are recorded except:\n    * `daily_sleep` table which is recorded for 24 users only.\n    * `weight_log` table which is recorded for only 8 users.\n\nThen, we will drop `weight_log` table as the sample is very low and any conclusions gained from it would be inaccurate and misleading.","metadata":{"_uuid":"fab1ca22-9fd8-4c02-bdfd-68fb2814aacc","_cell_guid":"6c3aff90-2ff8-43a4-ae85-a77f455558df","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Checking the unique values\nlength(unique(daily_activity$Id))\nlength(unique(daily_sleep$Id)) # The variable is recorded for 24 users only \nlength(unique(weight_log$Id)) # The variable is recorded for 8 users only (drop)\nlength(unique(hourly_steps$Id))\nlength(unique(hourly_calories$Id))\nlength(unique(hourly_intensities$Id))","metadata":{"_uuid":"60b1bc0e-3c77-46e8-814d-e30bd0681270","_cell_guid":"82c6d377-e93b-4d23-9ee2-15bd99683b31","collapsed":false,"_kg_hide-output":true,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:24.663179Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:24.664737Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:24.729386Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<span style=\"font-size:17px;\"><a id = \"subsection-three-two-five\"></a><u><b>Duplicate values</b></u></span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"e6e81b7e-ed1b-458c-9a5f-a6bb76191345","_cell_guid":"2462304c-eaf5-4c87-92f0-410de8e07e26","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Checking the duplicated values\nsum(duplicated(daily_activity))\nsum(duplicated(daily_sleep)) # 3 duplicate values need to be removed\nsum(duplicated(hourly_steps))\nsum(duplicated(hourly_calories))\nsum(duplicated(hourly_intensities))","metadata":{"_uuid":"36b209d6-0658-4405-ab6c-0bd0b503b8aa","_cell_guid":"47a86b9d-486a-4c20-8581-2a696fe8b2a5","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:24.732359Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:24.734021Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.167582Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<span style=\"font-size:17px;\"><a id = \"subsection-three-two-six\"></a><u><b>Check a sample of the dataset</b></u></span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"bb451ce2-6982-4363-8cbe-428f6c20da01","_cell_guid":"4fa8bc99-9e55-4e43-a273-993f40603db7","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"The data shows that in `daily_activity` table, there are some days in which the users do not use the tracker. Therefore, the `TotalSteps`, `TotalDistance` and all types of activities except `Sedentary` are *0's*.\n\nWe will check the number of these records to remove in the next step.","metadata":{"_uuid":"d953b972-e5fb-4fde-8724-42c93af7dc20","_cell_guid":"e598eba9-045f-48a8-b748-b58df3aa1f7e","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"daily_activity[sample(1:nrow(daily_activity), 15),]\ndaily_sleep[sample(1:nrow(daily_sleep), 15),]\nhourly_steps[sample(1:nrow(hourly_steps), 15),]\nhourly_calories[sample(1:nrow(hourly_calories), 15),]\nhourly_intensities[sample(1:nrow(hourly_intensities), 15),]","metadata":{"_uuid":"d4451c2f-55fd-4cc5-9ac6-85203e3a565f","_cell_guid":"c64dc857-aa05-4dc3-beaf-17ab27cc4bb2","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.172199Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.174642Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.302405Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<span style=\"font-size:17px;\"><a id = \"subsection-three-two-seven\"></a><u><b>Check the number of inactive usage days</b></u></span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"b4148453-7035-4bf3-8114-cbe0f21c442b","_cell_guid":"a0725b0a-13f9-4bad-8de7-34c735e0e2a9","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"There are **77 records** with inactive usage. Therefore, these records will be handled in the cleaning process.","metadata":{"_uuid":"0d9ab3b9-1663-41a3-a76e-dac6a6e3e3d0","_cell_guid":"afb12012-3f29-4439-b4c7-9b544251a748","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"inactive_usage <- daily_activity %>% \n  filter(TotalSteps == 0)\ninactive_usage","metadata":{"_uuid":"1721b923-b43e-4692-aa37-f8760ea043ee","_cell_guid":"ac52f4eb-c915-4a45-b081-280325b45433","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.305056Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.306513Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.495767Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"subsection-three-three\"></a>\n### **Cleaning data stage**","metadata":{"_uuid":"aa85d44c-93ee-4e00-bfb2-3aad253f8789","_cell_guid":"ecd33b0e-4bb9-451f-aea6-24cf0b0f0885","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"At first let's list the cleaning process steps in order to be more organized. The cleaning steps will procedd as the following order:\n1. Correcting the data types of `date` columns (transforming columns from character to datetime type).\n2. Cleaning column names (from *PascalCase* to *snake_case*) and renaming columns.\n3. Dropping duplicate values (in `sleep_day` table).\n4. Removing rows with 0 values in `TotalSteps` column in `activity_day` table.","metadata":{"_uuid":"0acd46a3-0425-4020-bc33-9ed39b749691","_cell_guid":"c41ec314-6e48-45d3-a7bd-a1ac4ae1250c","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<span style=\"font-size:17px;\"><a id = \"subsection-three-three-one\"></a><u><b>Correcting the data types of `date` columns</b></u></span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"e57849f9-cd36-4f80-a797-70d44ed465d0","_cell_guid":"8f031608-101a-4964-8890-9ee3ee845b07","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Correcting the data types (on daily basis tables)\ndaily_activity <- daily_activity %<>% \n  mutate(ActivityDate = as.Date(ActivityDate, \n                                format= \"%m/%d/%Y\"),\n         day_week = weekdays(ActivityDate)) %>% \n  select(-TrackerDistance) # dropping the tracker_distance column as it is redundant column\ndaily_activity <- daily_activity[c(1, 2, 15, 3:14)] #rearranging columns\n\ndaily_sleep <- daily_sleep %<>% \n  mutate(date = as.Date(SleepDay, format = \"%m/%d/%Y\")) %>%\n  select(-SleepDay)\ndaily_sleep <- daily_sleep[c(1, 5, 2:4)]","metadata":{"_uuid":"ed40c1e5-4834-450d-805f-99fc709fe6fa","_cell_guid":"02cd20b6-1d22-40d3-bbf0-5067641a0395","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.498528Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.500029Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.541873Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Correcting the data types (on hourly basis tables)\nhourly_steps <- data.frame(hourly_steps$Id,\n                           datetime = mdy_hms(hourly_steps$ActivityHour),\n                           hourly_steps$StepTotal)\n# In this step we make two column for date and time\nhourly_steps$date <- as.Date(hourly_steps$datetime, format = \"%m/%d/%Y\")\nhourly_steps$time <- format(as.POSIXct(hourly_steps$datetime),\n                          format = \"%H:%M:%S %p\")\n# dropping the datetime column as we no longer need it\nhourly_steps <- hourly_steps %>% \n  select(-datetime) \n# rearranging the columns\nhourly_steps <- hourly_steps[c(1, 3, 4, 2)]\n\n\nhourly_calories <- data.frame(hourly_calories$Id,\n                              datetime = mdy_hms(hourly_calories$ActivityHour),\n                              hourly_calories$Calories)\nhourly_calories$date <- as.Date(hourly_calories$datetime, format = \"%m/%d/%Y\")\nhourly_calories$time <- format(as.POSIXct(hourly_calories$datetime),\n                            format = \"%H:%M:%S %p\")\nhourly_calories <- hourly_calories %>% \n  select(-datetime) \nhourly_calories <- hourly_calories[c(1, 3, 4, 2)]\n\nhourly_intensities <- data.frame(hourly_intensities$Id,\n                                 datetime = mdy_hms(hourly_intensities$ActivityHour),\n                                 hourly_intensities$TotalIntensity,\n                                 hourly_intensities$AverageIntensity)\nhourly_intensities$date <- as.Date(hourly_intensities$datetime, format = \"%m/%d/%Y\")\nhourly_intensities$time <- format(as.POSIXct(hourly_intensities$datetime),\n                               format = \"%H:%M:%S %p\")\nhourly_intensities<- hourly_intensities %>% \n  select(-datetime) \nhourly_intensities <- hourly_intensities[c(1, 4, 5, 2, 3)]","metadata":{"_uuid":"a6f1579d-8337-4b04-9c96-79f4ccdb6738","_cell_guid":"035cbb2a-26b4-4577-a1e6-2c4af2a3fc72","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.544705Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.546163Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.820528Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<span style=\"font-size:17px;\"><a id = \"subsection-three-three-two\"></a><u><b>Cleaning column names (from PascalCase to *snake_case*) and renaming columns</b></u></span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"4871cd4a-1310-47e5-af4e-527ee1f123cc","_cell_guid":"3cdae532-02bd-4bed-8072-91113f39062f","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"activity_day <- clean_names(daily_activity) %>%\n  rename(date = activity_date)\n\nsleep_day <- clean_names(daily_sleep)\n\nsteps_hour <- hourly_steps %>% \n  rename(id=hourly_steps.Id, steps_total=hourly_steps.StepTotal)\n\ncalories_hour <- hourly_calories %>% \n  rename(id=hourly_calories.Id, calories=hourly_calories.Calories)\n\nintensities_hour <- hourly_intensities %>% \n  rename(id=hourly_intensities.Id,\n         total_intensity =hourly_intensities.TotalIntensity,\n         average_intensity=hourly_intensities.AverageIntensity)","metadata":{"_uuid":"4a6fe494-993f-4432-b5bd-aebea8ee3ada","_cell_guid":"8d22a2c9-70dc-42d8-bea0-f99c873acd62","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.823411Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.824877Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.938297Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<span style=\"font-size:17px;\"><a id = \"subsection-three-three-three\"></a><u><b>Dropping duplicate values (in `daily_sleep` table)</b></u></span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"c613a515-0b2b-41d1-93cc-e14e8ce5836d","_cell_guid":"45ca7de3-4d34-4e43-9f41-957790dacb27","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"After removing the duplicate values. We are left with **410 observations**.","metadata":{"_uuid":"5a25370e-ef04-4d26-b835-2fe371e59fba","_cell_guid":"f531b99a-6024-460e-9672-f00f9e0e0bfd","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"sleep_day <- distinct(sleep_day)","metadata":{"_uuid":"1a7dd3be-0083-410e-9172-44358051ca69","_cell_guid":"cafd67e7-e6fc-409a-aac7-bcc84a540de7","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.941112Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.942561Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.956417Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<span style=\"font-size:17px;\"><a id = \"subsection-three-three-four\"></a><u><b>Removing rows with 0 values in `TotalSteps` column in `activity_day` table</b></u></span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"2e5abc8d-2bd0-46bc-9a75-dba178f75ceb","_cell_guid":"5fcb1111-6ad1-4f8b-9fb8-ec236a0cf1f8","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"We need to remove these observations as they can skew the result and lead to inaccurate results. After removing the 77 observation with 0 values in `TotalSteps`. We will perform our calculations on the remaining **863 entries** and **33 users** .","metadata":{"_uuid":"e242994a-6f8e-4fcf-aa20-f5ac2ea0f68a","_cell_guid":"c21ef036-3401-4f86-9eb8-b62a396b32a9","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"activity_day <- activity_day %>% \n  filter(total_steps!= 0)","metadata":{"_uuid":"8702fda1-86a4-4cc5-aa5b-3350b7dcba89","_cell_guid":"3984c741-1bbb-4ae4-b0b2-5b48e26068e9","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.959364Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.960939Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.980821Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<span style=\"font-size:17px;\"><a id = \"subsection-three-three-five\"></a><u><b>Merging `sleep_day` and `activity_day` tables in one table `day_merged` and hour columns into one column `hour_merged`</b></u></span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"781a6116-ea79-448c-a6c2-1efd290a1c55","_cell_guid":"f0514c9d-bbc7-4d5a-a931-09a514ecd9ae","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Merging tables serves the following purposes:\n\n* `sleep_day` and `activity_day` will be merged to be able to apply comparisons between total minutes of sleeping and the activities performed by users.\n\n* Hour tables will be merged to spot the change of actvities, intensity of activities, and the calories burnt along the day.\n\n* we will keep `activity_day` table as it has more observations and users than the merged table, which will be useful in analyizing the activities of the users.\nAs the data demonstrates below: \n* `day_merged` table demonstrates that there are only **410 observations** and 24 users (instead of 33 that were in `activity_day` table).","metadata":{"_uuid":"117d47af-a5c0-4580-a3e3-f16533b20aec","_cell_guid":"64135375-0b3b-4dd9-b243-da3dd08785f4","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Merging day columns into one dataframe\nday_merged <- merge(activity_day, sleep_day, by = c('id', 'date'))\n# Merging hour columns into one dataframe\nstep_calory <- merge(steps_hour, calories_hour,by = c('id', 'date', 'time'))\nhour_merged <- merge(step_calory, intensities_hour,\n                     by = c('id', 'date', 'time'))","metadata":{"_uuid":"d4e81f6c-ab8c-4212-87e1-a309ba0a2329","_cell_guid":"68444b92-5b4f-4677-bbc1-3cea814249c8","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.983561Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:25.984992Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:26.66135Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<hr>","metadata":{"_uuid":"94348448-fd85-41e5-a472-5c281765a456","_cell_guid":"5b41f4bb-9548-47be-941f-46fb296cb705","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"![Analyze](https://img.freepik.com/free-vector/communication-flat-icon_1262-18771.jpg?t=st=1652007643~exp=1652008243~hmac=6450f6cfc55d9d17640eccaf96ed7d13b4e8e5da945f754db830cc2e71fb5e97&w=826)\n*Source:* <a href=\"https://www.freepik.com/vectors/office-character\">Office character vector created by katemangostar - www.freepik.com</a>","metadata":{"_uuid":"b30dc6c7-7cfc-4e2b-b857-b56112e8e366","_cell_guid":"09f98179-4423-4f7d-b6d9-e66b9bceb263","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# <span style=\"color:#FFBF00; font-size:27px; font-family:sans-serif;\"><a id=\"introduction\"> </a> Analyze Phase </span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"feca36de-2118-4ccd-9490-b6aed8c23d9b","_cell_guid":"374a122f-9485-45ba-951e-dc98c27187d1","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Get summary statistics of the types of activities in activity_day table\nactivity_day %>% \n  select(very_active_minutes, fairly_active_minutes, lightly_active_minutes,\n         sedentary_minutes) %>% \n  summary()\n\n# Get summary statistics of the total steps taken in activity_day table\nactivity_day %>% \n  select(total_steps) %>% \n  summary()\n\n# Get summary statistics of the sleep minutes taken in day_merged table\nday_merged %>% \n  select(total_minutes_asleep) %>% \n  summary()\n\n# Get the summary statistics of the total intensity per hour\nhour_merged %>%\n    select(steps_total, calories, total_intensity) %>%\n    summary()\nhour_merged","metadata":{"_uuid":"73e175ff-431e-443e-b9f7-83c9cff2b944","_cell_guid":"0f83f816-8731-417a-90e9-c3119eeb0f73","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:26.664211Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:26.665691Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:26.795994Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"As demonstrated in the summary statistics above:\n\n* Unfortunately, The average and median values of`sedentary_minutes` in `activity_day` table are high compared other types of activities.\n\n* The average total steps taken by users is **8319 steps** which considered good. However, the [CDC](https://www.cdc.gov/media/releases/2020/p0324-daily-step-count.html) propose the number of **12,000** steps per day in order to lower the risk of all-cause mortalities.\n\n* The average of sleeping minutes is 419 minutes (~ 7 hours) and the median is 432 minutes, which is great as the recommended sleep minutes for the adults according to [CDC](https://www.cdc.gov/sleep/features/getting-enough-sleep.html). As for the people who are not getting enough sleep, those can be targeted to improve their sleep habits.","metadata":{"_uuid":"3c60ff87-b971-40c6-941c-714b57b718fa","_cell_guid":"d9377785-45f4-4748-ac2b-7c221558c013","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Figure out the correlation coefficient between minutes of activities and sleep minutes\ncor(day_merged$sedentary_minutes, day_merged$total_minutes_asleep, method = \"pearson\")\ncor(day_merged$very_active_minutes, day_merged$total_minutes_asleep, method = \"pearson\")\ncor(day_merged$fairly_active_minutes, day_merged$total_minutes_asleep, method = \"pearson\")\ncor(day_merged$lightly_active_minutes, day_merged$total_minutes_asleep, method = \"pearson\")\n\n# Figure out the correlation coefficient between minutes of activities and calories\ncor(day_merged$sedentary_minutes, day_merged$calories, method = \"pearson\")\ncor(day_merged$very_active_minutes, day_merged$calories, method = \"pearson\")\ncor(day_merged$fairly_active_minutes, day_merged$calories, method = \"pearson\")\ncor(day_merged$lightly_active_minutes, day_merged$calories, method = \"pearson\")","metadata":{"_uuid":"08c5dbd8-fe05-43d0-ab37-4d8a8e5a1368","_cell_guid":"f65b7f7b-a996-4a6f-b0f0-1e3a7e2c470f","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:26.798627Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:26.800056Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:26.855531Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"The correlation coefficients between variable can help us understand the type and strenght of the interrelationship amond variables to guide our analysis.\n\n* The correlation coefficient for the level of activitiy minutes and sleep minutes demonstrates some interesting insights:\n    \n   * As expected, there is a moderately strong negative relationship between the sedentary minutes and sleeping minutes, so that as the sedentary minutes increase the sleeping minutes tend to decrease causing sleeping issues.\n   \n   * Surprisingly, there is weak or no association among the other levels of activities and sleeping minutes. This can be caused by the small sample set or small number of observations.\n   \n* The correlation coefficient for the level of activitiy minutes and calories burnt below demonstrates some interesting insights:\n\n    * There is a strong postive relationship between the active minutes and level of calories burnt.\n    * The rest of activities also have a positive relationship with the calories burnt but it is very weak.","metadata":{"_uuid":"93a76e8c-b1e2-422e-8b88-93fd3271d63d","_cell_guid":"b5924797-2958-4877-b1ae-68ae085c3d3c","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# The activty tracker usage by the 33 users from `activity_day` table\n# inspired by: Vickie Liu \"https://www.kaggle.com/vickie06\"\nactivity_tracker <- activity_day %>%\n  group_by(id) %>%\n  summarize(active_usage = sum(n())) %>%\n  arrange(-active_usage) %>%\n  select(active_usage)\nsummary(activity_tracker, active_usage)\n\n# The sleep tracker usage by the 24 users from `day_merged` table\nsleep_tracker <- day_merged %>%\n  group_by(id) %>%\n  summarize(sleep_usage = sum(n())) %>%\n  arrange(-sleep_usage) %>%\n  select(sleep_usage)\nsummary(sleep_tracker, sleep_usage)","metadata":{"_uuid":"2e0651ba-c637-4a74-b0eb-c634c759df98","_cell_guid":"e28443d4-82eb-4eda-95d4-cb3959da5e32","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:26.858117Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:26.859568Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:26.935242Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"The summary statistics for both activity trackers and sleep trackers demonstrates the following results:\n\n* The median of activity tracker usage is about 31 days.\n\n* The median of sleep tracker usage is about 20.5 days.","metadata":{"_uuid":"e13fdd2f-69ac-4fa7-8fca-1dff245178f0","_cell_guid":"6dff1522-e3e8-40cd-9f90-f76728afb385","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"![Share](https://img.freepik.com/free-vector/people-analyzing-growth-charts_23-2148866843.jpg?t=st=1652022473~exp=1652023073~hmac=5075a8d9119d3fe6da39754514e68133ea4ec6b77703cc24da37a1e56c6438df&w=996)\n*Source:* <a href=\"https://www.freepik.com/vectors/business-statistics\">Business statistics vector created by freepik - www.freepik.com</a>","metadata":{"_uuid":"43639f64-1fd0-403f-abb8-fcb639ba0759","_cell_guid":"c926033b-a33d-42a0-ad5f-417239757414","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<hr>","metadata":{"_uuid":"51b2e962-c45b-48c0-bf54-b0cc03aa0967","_cell_guid":"dba14155-88ff-43ce-96a1-7ecd0041fa9e","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# <span style=\"color:#FFBF00; font-size:27px; font-family:sans-serif;\"><a id=\"introduction\"> </a> Share Phase </span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"5acd90b7-f93c-4e89-a44b-d69401a984a3","_cell_guid":"287d0893-7982-4e61-8e2a-beff4c788922","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Now let's build our visualizations to better understand our case and share our insights with the stakeholders in Bellabeat to lead them to a successful marketing campaign","metadata":{"_uuid":"d0f91bf1-f839-4aad-86ac-d3c8bb7a7216","_cell_guid":"da8f4c06-576a-4e33-b402-2e1cb6037296","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### <b> Findings </b>\n\n* The pie chart assures our summary statistics above that most of users nearly perform no acivities.\n\n* This segement needs to be focused on and be aware of the health risks of that.","metadata":{"_uuid":"2e637a32-73ed-4f35-8ad2-22b9c5e703ee","_cell_guid":"55d404b2-df10-4a70-8268-542d43853d03","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Get the percentage of minutes taken by each type of activities along the day\nintense_total_minutes <- sum(activity_day$fairly_active_minutes,\n                             activity_day$very_active_minutes,\n                             activity_day$lightly_active_minutes,\n                             activity_day$sedentary_minutes)\n\n\nintense_share_minutes <- data.frame(\"intensity\" = c(\"Very active\", \"Fairly active\",\n                                                    \"Lightly active\", \"Sedentary\"),\n                                    \"share\" = c(sum(activity_day$fairly_active_minutes)/intense_total_minutes,\n                                                sum(activity_day$lightly_active_minutes)/intense_total_minutes,\n                                                sum(activity_day$very_active_minutes)/intense_total_minutes,\n                                                sum(activity_day$sedentary_minutes)/intense_total_minutes))\n\npie_intensity_minutes <- ggplot(intense_share_minutes, aes(x = \"\", y=share, fill=intensity)) +\n                            geom_bar(stat=\"identity\", width=1) + coord_polar(\"y\", start=0) + geom_col() + \ngeom_text(aes(label = paste0(round(share*100), \"%\"), x = 1.6),\n          position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5)) +\nscale_fill_manual(values=c(\"#55DDE0\", \"#33658A\", \"#F6AE2D\", \"#F26419\")) + \nlabs(x = NULL, y = NULL, fill = NULL, title = \"Daily Intensity level (Minutes)\")+ \ntheme_classic() + theme(axis.line = element_blank(),\n                        axis.text = element_blank(),\n                        axis.ticks = element_blank(),\n                        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5,\n                                                  size = 15, color = \"#666666\", face = 'bold'))\npie_intensity_minutes","metadata":{"_uuid":"dfa89e4f-8841-46c3-a621-4bf70b1b3ac5","_cell_guid":"6d15f5b6-3908-487e-be6b-ec35e7b48944","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:26.938083Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:26.939653Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:27.624391Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### <b> Findings </b>\n\nAs shwon in the figures below, The best form of intensity to lose more calories is the very active form of training. In contrast, as the minutes of sedentary times increases, it reduces the rate of calories burnt which may lead to *obesity*.","metadata":{"_uuid":"5ec12602-ec12-4e0a-bf90-6b356a9b9cc7","_cell_guid":"c301ce51-668f-4752-8fcc-f14ac2b83819","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Relationship between intensity of activity minutes and calories burnt\nactive_1 <- ggplot(activity_day, aes(x = very_active_minutes, y = calories)) +\n                     geom_point(color=\"#FDD017\") + geom_smooth() +\n                     theme(legend.position=\"none\") + \n                     labs(title=\"Very active minutes vs. Calories\",\n                          x = \"Minutes\",\n                          y = \"Calories\")\nactive_2 <- ggplot(activity_day, aes(x = fairly_active_minutes, y = calories)) +\n                     geom_point(color=\"#52D017\") + geom_smooth() +\n                     theme(legend.position=\"none\") + \n                     labs(title=\"Fairly active minutes vs. Calories\",\n                          x = \"Minutes\",\n                          y = \"Calories\")\nactive_3 <- ggplot(activity_day, aes(x = lightly_active_minutes, y = calories))+\n                     geom_point(color=\"#990000\") + geom_smooth() +\n                     theme(legend.position=\"none\") + \n                     labs(title=\"Lightly active minutes vs. Calories\",\n                          x = \"Minutes\",\n                          y = \"Calories\")\nactive_4 <- ggplot(activity_day, aes(x = sedentary_minutes, y = calories)) +\n                     geom_point(color=\"#57FEFF\") + geom_smooth() +\n                     theme(legend.position=\"none\") + \n                     labs(title=\"Sedentary minutes vs. Calories\",\n                          x = \"Minutes\",\n                          y = \"Calories\")\n\nggarrange(active_1,active_2,active_3,active_4)","metadata":{"_uuid":"c0794f1f-2c8d-408c-b0ff-73efac7b3467","_cell_guid":"72914fa1-c169-4b94-89f7-279528fd8a66","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:27.627063Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:27.628486Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:30.319339Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Relationship between intensity of activity minutes and minutes of sleeping\nactive_sleep <- ggplot(data = day_merged, aes(x =very_active_minutes,\n                                               y=total_minutes_asleep)) +\n                  geom_point(color = \"#FDD017\")+ geom_smooth(method = 'lm', se = TRUE)+\n                  labs(title = \"Very active minutes vs. Sleep\",\n                       x = \"Activity Minutes\",\n                       y = \"Sleep minutes\")\nfairly_sleep <- ggplot(data = day_merged, aes(x =fairly_active_minutes,\n                                              y=total_minutes_asleep)) +\n                  geom_point(color = \"#52D017\")+ geom_smooth(method = 'lm', se = TRUE)+\n                  labs(title = \"Fairly active minutes vs. Sleep\",\n                       x = \"Activity Minutes\",\n                       y = \"Sleep minutes\")\nlightly_sleep <- ggplot(data = day_merged, aes(x =lightly_active_minutes,\n                                              y=total_minutes_asleep)) +\n                  geom_point(color = \"#990000\")+ geom_smooth(method = 'lm', se = TRUE)+\n                  labs(title = \"Lightly active minutes vs. Sleep\",\n                       x = \"Activity Minutes\",\n                       y = \"Sleep minutes\")\nsedentary_sleep <- ggplot(data = day_merged, aes(x =sedentary_minutes,\n                                              y=total_minutes_asleep)) +\n                  geom_point(color = \"#57FEFF\")+ geom_smooth(method = 'lm', se = TRUE)+\n                  labs(title = \"Sedentary minuutes vs. Sleep\",\n                       x = \"Activity Minutes\",\n                       y = \"Sleep minutes\")\nggarrange(active_sleep, fairly_sleep, lightly_sleep,sedentary_sleep, nrow=2,ncol=2)","metadata":{"_uuid":"53c3495c-55f3-4ecf-8697-ddbc056d922d","_cell_guid":"688962ca-af69-4f91-bd3b-b564daede99d","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:30.322155Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:30.323662Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:31.251616Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### <b> Findings </b>\n\nThere is a weak positive correlation between Total steps taken by each user and the calories burnt, according to the equation above as steps increase by 1 step the burnt calories will increase by 0.083.","metadata":{"_uuid":"29c48833-75d5-4947-bfd5-d747cd92fd31","_cell_guid":"04af41f5-98ed-4972-a4e0-d476453b5c33","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Relationship between total steps and calories\nstep_cal<- ggplot(data = activity_day, aes(x = total_steps, y = calories)) +\n              geom_point()+\n              geom_smooth(method = 'lm', se = TRUE) +\n              stat_regline_equation(label.y = 5000, aes(label = ..eq.label..))+\n              stat_regline_equation(label.y = 4600, aes(label = ..rr.label..))+\n              labs(title = \"Relationship between Total Steps vs. Calories\",\n                   x = \"Total Steps\",\n                   y = \"Calories\")\nstep_cal","metadata":{"_uuid":"449839f6-2fa5-4b48-bee9-d43d057e20da","_cell_guid":"9858d905-f616-410b-a4e4-238175949a8b","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:31.254326Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:31.255805Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:31.669323Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### <b> Findings </b>\n\nThe average intensity distribution is approximately skewed to the left meaning that the intensity of users' activities begin to increase starting from the dawn (5 a.m) and reach the peak point at nearly the sunset time (6 p.m).\n\nThe same cocnept can be applied on the average steps taken along the day, as the average staps tend to be at its peak between 5 a.m and 6 p.m.","metadata":{"_uuid":"74cddfc9-0d84-4ecd-80b6-160f52552160","_cell_guid":"3fb605c1-5a2a-40dd-bb25-aab82867201f","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Figure out the common hour of training during the day\ncommon_h <- hour_merged  %>%\n              group_by(time) %>%\n              summarize(common = sum(calories))\n   \n\ncommon_hour <- ggplot(common_h, aes(x = time, y = common)) +\n                 geom_col(stat = \"identity\", fill = \"darkgreen\") +\n                 theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90)) +\n                 labs(title = \"Most common hour of activity\",\n                     x = \"Time\", y = \"Common hour\")\n                 \ncommon_hour","metadata":{"_uuid":"72c13c65-8176-4a74-a934-886f77b78073","_cell_guid":"beb18d59-2151-4a82-92d5-98f8d64a7c12","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:31.672104Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:31.6736Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:31.918415Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"intense_hour <- hour_merged %>% \n  group_by(time) %>% \n  summarise(average_total_intense = mean(total_intensity)) \n\nintense_hour_fig <- ggplot(intense_hour, aes(x = time, y = average_total_intense,\n                         fill = average_total_intense)) + \n                geom_col(stat = 'identity')+\n                theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90)) +\n                labs(title = \"Average intensity per hour\",\n                subtitle = \"Plot of intensity by minutes\",\n                     x = \"Time\", y = \"Average intensity\") +\n                scale_fill_gradient(low = \"lightblue\", high = \"darkblue\")\nintense_hour_fig","metadata":{"_uuid":"e97c8d44-4c49-44b9-80af-f9a80dc7f638","_cell_guid":"ad27d47c-1169-43e1-9560-a3a214be8ab1","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:31.92139Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:31.9229Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:32.248875Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"steps_hour <- hour_merged %>% \n  group_by(time) %>% \n  summarise(average_steps = mean(steps_total)) \n\nstep_hour_fig <- ggplot(steps_hour, aes(x = time, y = average_steps,\n                         fill = average_steps)) + \n                        geom_col(stat = 'identity')+\n                        theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90)) +\n                        labs(title = \"Average steps per hour\",\n                             x = \"Time\", y = \"Average steps\") +\n                        scale_fill_gradient(low = \"green\", high = \"red\")\nstep_hour_fig","metadata":{"_uuid":"3b7a752c-10b6-4f02-bce5-93d595447309","_cell_guid":"1640215c-71a8-4db0-83c9-54247648bc3c","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-12T10:57:32.251755Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-12T10:57:32.253275Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-12T10:57:32.552468Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<hr>","metadata":{"_uuid":"4ea7dc22-43e4-4985-91c1-c8938ece6ad7","_cell_guid":"8939c343-b597-46b1-8f97-efcc68d25dbe","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"![Final](https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1510017803434-a899398421b3?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&ixid=MnwxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8&auto=format&fit=crop&w=870&q=80)","metadata":{"_uuid":"eb77225f-f453-4eba-80b3-0eef9346c34f","_cell_guid":"5009fc88-0af9-4dad-b47a-c4d3e6cf71f0","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# <span style=\"color:#FFBF00; font-size:27px; font-family:sans-serif;\"><a id=\"introduction\"> </a> Final insights and recommendations </span>","metadata":{"_uuid":"181f402f-bb28-4eaf-8bcc-c6f76ee3247e","_cell_guid":"f08e976c-1e3a-45fb-adac-2c49c1b8c9ae","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"The target audience for **Bellabeat** is women. Unfortunately the dataset that we have does not demonstrate demographics about the users based on their genders. However, we will assume that the insights that we came up with would apply on both genders. The insights that we came up with the dataset with us are:","metadata":{"_uuid":"8815725d-9a4c-400c-8535-c3479b67553b","_cell_guid":"6f40ad5f-6aab-4238-81fb-170584dd4080","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<span style=\"font-size:20px; color:#F39C12;\"><b> Insight 1 </b></span>\n\n* Sedentary or inactive lifestyle take up **~79 percent** of the activity tracker day, which has to be focused on during the marketing campaign and focus more on the people that exert little or no efforts  along the day as those people are exposed more to have unfavorable health conditions **(e.g. obesity)**.\n\n* The marketing campaign has to have an awareness role to inform people how it is important to be active which in return lead to be in shape.\n\n<span style=\"font-size:20px; color:#F39C12;\"><b>Insight 2</b></span>\n\n* Users tend to use activity trackers more than sleep trackers as the median of users of activity trackers is **30 users** compared to **20.5 users** for sleep trackers. Therefore, the marketing campaign should pay attention to sleep trackers users as this market segment has more room for growth in alignment with retaining or increasing the activity tracker users.\n\n<span style=\"font-size:20px; color:#F39C12;\"><b>Insight 3</b></span>\n\n* Apparently, the campaign should target the ativity trackers' users at the times between **05:00** AM and **22:00 PM** and the rest of day the sleep trackers can be targeted.\n\n* The process can take the shape of sending **notifications** to the users about the best practices to achieve the most benefit from activities or getting the perfect sleeping times.","metadata":{"_uuid":"a555b80f-45e3-4526-aef4-ef0485bd6eac","_cell_guid":"ac70fd74-16ec-422c-98fa-7917c02df932","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<span style=\"font-size:20px; color:#F39C12;\"><b> Recommendations </b></span>\n\nAnd our recommendations to the campaign are listed in the following table:","metadata":{"_uuid":"698ef1ef-7ce9-4454-9cf6-156e3efbc4a8","_cell_guid":"5d42a867-45ae-4b0c-8779-5418aa047251","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"| Feature               | Description  |\n|:---------------------------:|:-------------------:|\n|**Notification System**   | Building a notification system that notify the user about the  best practices on the recommended time to walk, sleep and the ideal amount of sleeping or steps to walk along the day based on characteristics of the user can be very effective in the marketing campaign|\n|**Reward System**| The company can also provide the sense of entertainment while using its products and services. So, the company can hold somthing like a competition among the users of its products (e.g. The top 10 users who were the most active during the day) and accordingly provide various types of rewards to the users, which contribute to retain the current users and increase their loyalty in addition to bringing new customers|\n|**New Upgrades**| Upgrading the software (e.g easier user interface) or the hardware (e.g more lasting battery) is the basic features that any consumer will love to find in the smart product that he uses on a regualr base along the day|","metadata":{"_uuid":"f57f0ecf-6fb9-4e4a-9649-7e1ad24be38c","_cell_guid":"5ee5746d-3032-4066-ac15-f22d256458a4","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Finally, I would like to thank you for sticking with us up till now and I hope this project added a value to you. I really appreciate your valued time 🙏.","metadata":{"_uuid":"624b9e94-cc99-4e64-952c-6624908504ff","_cell_guid":"a8998ff5-b688-4bd9-8cc5-a07ebf561fcd","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<hr>","metadata":{"_uuid":"5ba9f076-8645-415f-aea1-5924c4952ad4","_cell_guid":"819100eb-75d6-4cee-b375-02322ae9d68f","trusted":true}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<span style=\"color:#F26301;font-size:20px;\"><i>Sources of inspiration</i></span>\n\n1. Capstone - Case Study Bellabeat by [Macarena Lacasa](https://www.kaggle.com/macarenalacasa) \n\n2. Bellabeat Capstone Project in R by [ZULKHAIREE SULAIMAN](https://www.kaggle.com/zulkhaireesulaiman) \n\n3. Bellabeat Biz Insight with R_Case Study by [VICKIE LIU](https://www.kaggle.com/vickie06)","metadata":{"_uuid":"1c321723-1513-4ea7-a96c-7b45ce94f7e7","_cell_guid":"b4ac1aff-b7e7-4993-a967-b5345cba84df","trusted":true}}]}